				<p><p>The magnetometer is an electric compass. If you know the magnetic field that you are operating in, you should be able to tell which direction you're pointing in. </p>

<p>All three sensors can be fused together to give you an accurate estimate of attitude. This can be done using a nonlinear kalman filter.</p>

<p>Using only the accelerometer and the gyro, vehicle heading cannot be measured. You can integrate the gyro measurements but you have no way to account for drift. That is what the magnetometer brings to the system.</p>
